Farming is not on most Chinese graduates' radar. But the rural revitalization strategy is transforming poor villages and a growing number of university graduates are willing to go home to be farmers. CGTN's reporter Huang Yichang visited Xijiangzhai - a once highly impoverished village in central China's Kaifeng city, Henan Provinceï¼Œto explore how the improved rural environment and new opportunities are attracting more talented youth back home to join farming, and how these new farmers are giving a new meaning to the word "farmer."